If this is server code, you should avoid synchronous functions as much as possible once the server is handling requests. During the initial server startup, synchronous code is fine though. Synchronous code will block the event loop and prevent your server from doing anything else until the synchronous code completes (unless you're using multiple threads). Asynchronous functions will return a `Promise` that will either resolve or reject depending on whether or not the function is successful or not.

You should also try to avoid checking if something exists before using it (`cacheDir` in your example). This is a [TOCTOU race condition](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use). It's usually better to try to perform some operation, and handle the error if one happens.

