If it opened without error, then your data could not have been cached, thus you would asynchronously write into the [file](https://doc.deno.land/deno/stable/~/Deno.FsFile), otherwise returning your cached data.

```js
Deno.open(cachedDirectory, { createNew: true }).then(
 // it wasn't cached
 (file) => {
  const renderResult = render();
  file.write(renderResult);
  return renderResult;
 },
 // it was cached
 (_error) => <img href={cacheDir} />
);
```

