There is a bit about a single `&` for async [here](https://deno.land/manual@v1.27.2/tools/task_runner#async-commands) but in normal shells, that would background the first process and run the next, which is not quite the same (the first process would be straggling in the background). It's not really the native unix-shell, though, it's a cross-platform subset of sh that deno runs (so it works same on windows), so it works as-is on all platforms with `&`.

