@johynpapin Ah I understood your question now (Thanks @XiNiHa).

1. As I mentioned above, the gRPC client and server is made from protobuf codegen such as protobuf.js, pbkit or protoc plugins. There is a various taste of client and server interface and requiring RPC code generation so supporting those functionality on Deno directly is too opinionated. The same goes for implementing all serialization formats that support gRPC into Deno directly.
2. The API I proposed (`Deno.connectGrpc` and `Deno.listenGrpc`) is not related to support Connect or gRPC-Web. Because It already can be implemented in userland with `fetch` and `Deno.serveHttp` and they will have different detailed interfaces so they should be wrapped in a higher abstraction on user level anyway.

