This is how modules work, and how they interact with scripts: the global scope of the module is private to each module, and functions declared in it without exposing them anywhere else aren't available to other modules or scripts. It works the same way with modules and scripts in the web:

```html
<script type="module">
  console.log("Hello world!");
  function test() {}
</script>

<script>
  // We wait for the load event to make sure the module runs first.
  window.addEventListener("load", () => {
    test();
  });
</script>
```

