To properly exit `Deno.serve` with a zero exit code, use an `AbortController` to signal the server shutdown. This prevents Deno from automatically returning a 130 code:

```ts
const controller = new AbortController();
const { signal } = controller;

Deno.serve({ signal }, async (req) => {
  return new Response("Hello World");
});

Deno.addSignalListener("SIGINT", async () => {
  console.log("Caught SIGINT, shutting down...");
  controller.abort(); // Gracefully shut down server
  await client.destroy();
  db.close();
  kv.close();
  Deno.exit(0); // Ensure zero exit code
});
```

